<p>I remember when I was about eight or nine, I had a pet. It was my first pet, actually, and it was a little budgie called Ollie. 
I named her Ollie because it was the year of the Olympics … I can't remember which year it was. But this bird was really unusual because, quite quickly she became very tame. 
And I used to come home from school and I'd pick her up off whatever she was perching and I'd take her upstairs  and she'd sit on the side of the bed. 
I don't know what actually happened to her because one day,  we all got so used to just her being round the house,  that one day my mother came in with some washing, 
the back door was open, and she just flew off and, er, we never found her again. It's a bit sad, really …</p>

<vim-test>
  <vim-test-question>
    <vim-test-question-text>The best title is...</vim-test-question-text>
