<p>It was a time when I was really frightened and  it was about two years ago,  when I was on holiday in Sicily. And one afternoon we decided to hire a boat to go and sail round the coast. 
It started off quite nicely, it was, the sun was shining and, you know, we were sunbathing.  But then we decided to drop the anchor and stay still for a little while, 
but I didn't know that you shouldn't use the engine when the anchor is dropped.  So somehow the rope got tangled up  in the engine and the engine stopped working.</p>

